# Job Search Profile

> **Edit this file with your own background and target roles.** The pipeline
> uses it to give Claude context when summarizing job descriptions and ranking
> matches. The more specific you are, the better the matching.

## Background
- **Current role:** {{your current job title and company, e.g. "Marketing Manager at Acme Corp"}}
- **Total experience:** {{years and a one-line summary, e.g. "8 years across B2B SaaS marketing"}}
- **Education:** {{degree, school, year}}

## Target roles
List the role titles and levels you're targeting. Be inclusive — the pipeline
runs a separate search per role. Examples:
- {{Senior Marketing Manager}}
- {{Director of Marketing}}
- {{Head of Growth}}

## Core skills / specialties
What you bring to a role — used by the scorer to weight title relevance.
Examples: `B2B demand gen`, `SEO`, `paid acquisition`, `Hubspot`, `lifecycle marketing`.

## Search constraints
- **Locations:** {{e.g. New York, NY · Remote (US) · Boston, MA}}
- **Salary floor:** {{e.g. $130,000 base — filters out junior roles}}
- **Job type:** {{Full-time / Contract / Either}}
- **Anything else:** {{e.g. "must offer health benefits", "no agencies", etc.}}
